  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with Type 2 Diabetes randomly allocated to the intervention arm (health coaching +
      smartphone-based health promotion software) will have significantly better Hemoglobin A1c
      levels at 6 months post-intervention than patients with Type 2 Diabetes allocated to the
      control arm (health coaching alone).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Inclusion criteria: all participating patients have been diagnosed with Type 2 Diabetes, are
      between 25 and 70 years of age, have a regular primary care physician, and have HbA1c levels
      &gt; or = to 7.3.

      Exclusion criteria: Axis I and II psychiatric disorders.

      Primary outcome: HBA1c at 6 months follow up.

      Secondary outcome: Centre for Epidemiological Studies Depression Scale
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
